\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 26. R. confertus} Willd.,{\i  Enum. Pl. Horti Berol. }397 (1809). Perennial up to 80 cm, papillose-pubescent. Basal leaves deeply cordate-triangular, scarcely longer than wide, the basal lobes and apex rounded; petiole often longer than the lamina. Axis of panicle flexuous; branches arcuate at the base. Valves c. 6 × 8 mm, broadly reniform-scutate, with small, irregular, indistinct teeth near the base, 1 with a small tubercle. 2n = 40.{\i  Mainly ruderal. E. & E.C. Europe; C. Appennini.} Cz Hu It ?Po Rm Rs(N, B, C, W, K, E)[Br Fe].
