\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 27. R. hydrolapathum} Hudson,{\i  Fl. Angl}. ed. 2, 154 (1778). Perennial up to 200 cm. Leaves flat, suberect, broadly lanceolate, tapering equally at both ends, lateral veins at a right-angle to the midrib; basal leaves 4-5 times as long as wide. Pedicels stiff, c. 1½ times as long as the valves. Valves triangular, each with a distinct, fusiform tubercle. Nut 4·5-5 mm. 2n = 200.{\i  Marshes and beside lakes and rivers. Most of Europe, from} 62°{\i  N. in Finland to} 40°{\i  N. in Italy, but very local in the south}. Al Au Be Br Bu Cz Da Fe Ga Ge Gr Hb He Ho Hs Hu It Ju No Po Rm Rs(N, B, C, W, E) Sa Su.
