\pard\f0\fs28 The hybrid with{\b  20} ({\i R. heterophyllus} C.F. Schultz,{\i  R. maximus} Schreber, non C.C. Gmelin) is frequent in N.C. Europe and S. Fennoscandia. It is similar in habit to {\b 27} but has wider and shorter leaves, rounded or slightly cordate at the base, and valves of somewhat irregular development, in part larger and wider than in {\b 27}. The hybrid with {\b 37} is rarer, but not infrequent in England and the Netherlands; it is similar in habit to {\b 27} but easily distinguished by the distinct teeth near the base of the valves and by their rather long apex.
